This was developed with the help of 

1. Can you run Intel's Data-plane Development Kit (DPDK) in a container?  Yep.

  http://developerblog.redhat.com/2015/06/02/can-you-run-intels-data-plane-development-kit-dpdk-in-a-docker-container-yep/

  
2. https://github.com/jeremyeder/docker-dpdk


Please edit rhel subscription manager USERNAME and PASSWORD or else set up yum in DOCKERFILE.

Then run the install-image-with-docker.sh with administrative privillage to create a docker container with dpdk build and running capabilities.

